The Centre of Australian Category Theory (CoACT) is currently =
advertising an 18 month Research Fellowship in Category Theory.

This role is open to application by mathematicians who have a strong =
research interest and growing reputation in the field of Category Theory =
and whose PhD was awarded no earlier than 2008. The successful candidate =
will work on the Australian Research Council Discovery Grant entitled:
=20
DP1094883 Applicable Categorical Structures".
=20
The successful candidate will collaborate with members of Macquarie =
University's Centre of Australian Category Theory (CoACT) to advance the =
scientific program supported by this grant. As part of this activity the =
appointee will be expected to take an active part in the overall =
activities of the CoACT research centre, to present research progress =
regularly at the Australian Category Seminar and to publish papers in =
well regarded mathematical journals. Where appropriate the appointee may =
also be asked to assist with the mathematical supervision of CoACT's PhD =
research students.
=20
Essential Selection Criteria: PhD in Category Theory or a closely =
related area of Mathematics (or submitted); a publication record in =
Category Theory; a demonstrated ability to present research results at =
scientific meetings and to publish in the scientific literature; good =
written and oral communication skills.
=20
Desirable Selection Criteria: A background in Higher Category Theory or =
Monoidal Category Theory and their applications to Homotopy Theory, =
Algebraic Topology, Algebraic Geometry, Computer Science or Mathematical =
Physics.
=20
Applications for this position should be made online, and details of how =
to do this can be obtained by clicking on the "Access Externally =
Advertised Jobs" link at the following URL http://www.jobs.mq.edu.au/. =
Look for the job entitled "Research Fellow in Mathematics" with the =
requisition ID 016LM.
=20
Further Enquiries: Associate Professor Dominic Verity, email: =
dominic.verity@mq.edu.au or telephone +61 2 9850 9522.
=20
Appointment Type: Full-time, fixed-term for a period of 18 months. =
Probationary conditions may apply.
=20
Package: Level A from AUD $71,597.00 - $76,801.00 per annum, plus 9% =
employer's superannuation contribution and annual leave loading.
=20
Applications Close: Friday, 30 December 2011
=20
Macquarie University is an EO Employer committed to diversity and social =
inclusion. Applications are encouraged from people with a disability; =
women (particularly for senior and non-traditional roles); Indigenous =
Australians, people who identify as GLBTI; and those from culturally and =
linguistically diverse backgrounds
=20
Applications need to be submitted through the Macquarie University =
online recruitment system. Where circumstances such as disability or =
remote location prohibit your access to our online system please contact =
the enquiries person listed in this advertisement for assistance.



